🚀 Day 30/30 of My SQL Challenge

Today I solved LeetCode Problem 262 – Trips and Users on LeetCode.

📌 Problem Overview
We are given two tables: Trips and Users.
The task is to calculate the daily cancellation rate of trips between 2013-10-01 and 2013-10-03, considering only those trips where both the client and the driver are not banned.

Cancellation Rate =
(Number of cancelled trips) / (Total trips per day)

Cancelled trips include:
• cancelled_by_driver
• cancelled_by_client

💻 SQL Source Code

SELECT 
    t.request_at AS Day,
    ROUND(
        SUM(CASE 
                WHEN t.status IN ('cancelled_by_driver','cancelled_by_client') 
                THEN 1 ELSE 0 
            END) / COUNT(*),
        2
    ) AS "Cancellation Rate"
FROM Trips t
JOIN Users c 
    ON t.client_id = c.users_id 
    AND c.banned = 'No'
JOIN Users d 
    ON t.driver_id = d.users_id 
    AND d.banned = 'No'
WHERE t.request_at BETWEEN '2013-10-01' AND '2013-10-03'
GROUP BY t.request_at;
